    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="886"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51 Public Works Debt/298</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 84</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-28">March 28,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received April 1.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to my despatch No. 49
                    of March 19, 1940, with which I transmitted memoranda covering conversations
                    with the Secretary of State, Dr. Campa, and with the President, Dr. Laredo Brú.
                    In view of further information which came into my possession, I deemed it
                    advisable to seek another conversation with the President, and was able to do so
                    on March 25, 1940. There is transmitted herewith a memorandum of my
                        conversation<note n="29" xml:id="d886fn1">Not printed. Ambassador
                        Messersmith informed the Cuban President and Secretary of State of reported
                        activities by certain persons to delay action in an effort to get some
                        personal advantage from the settlement of the public works debt.</note> with
                    him which <pb facs="0762" n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/> is self-explanatory and
                    which I believe the Department will find of interest.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George S. Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
